The paper focuses on pedestrian detection using deep learning frameworks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method involves modeling semantic attributes and using a novel Non-Maximum Suppression technique, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a ground truth target and evaluation on benchmark datasets, indicating the involvement of robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
